Vercel Speed Insights Implementation
=====================================

Successfully implemented Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js project.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed @vercel/speed-insights version 1.3.1
- Updated package.json with the new dependency
- Updated package-lock.json with the complete dependency tree

### 2. Root Layout Update (src/app/layout.tsx)
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, placed after `{children}`
- This follows the recommended pattern for Next.js 13.5+ with App Router

## Implementation Details:

The project uses:
- Next.js 16.1.6 (App Router)
- npm as the package manager
- TypeScript with strict type checking

The implementation follows Vercel's official documentation for Next.js App Router integration:
- Used the `/next` export which is optimized for App Router
- Placed the component at the root layout level for site-wide tracking
- No additional configuration needed - the component works automatically

